<br>
In my personal opinion, I think the nostalgia factor plays a role in this too.  People remember back to the days when they were younger, back when RPGs and videogames actually gave you a thrill and got your heart racing.  I'm sure they were playing FF6 (FF3) then, and I'm sure that was one of those times.  Back, when they were younger, Kefka was a brilliant villain.  As they're older, they remember back to those times, and realize how cool he was THEN.  Had they JUST started playing FF6 now, I don't think it would've gone over well.  I mean, if FF6 came out TODAY, and everyone started playing it, would it be a hit?  I doubt it.  I really love Chrono Trigger, but if I went out and bought it today, there's a chance I may opinion on it may be less than when I got it 5 years ago.  That's what the nostalgia factor is, people holding onto memories and feeling THOSE were good times, as they will feel about the present times in 10 years.<br>
<br>
Well, sorry about trailing off, about Kefka, what do you think? <p><hr>
