<br>
I think the biggest success in FFX was the voice acting.  It added a whole new dimension to the game, and made it that much more enjoyable, also helping make the characters feel more realistic.<br>
<br>
Also, as much as people don't know it, or seem to ignore it, music is an integral part in a game.  Music really sets the mood of the game.  Again, I'll use FFX as an example, it had a great soundtrack.  There was ALOT of mood in FFX, mostly from the music.<br>
<br>
Not to say gameplay, challenge, and story aren't important, because they are, I'm just saying how important graphics and music are as well. <p><hr>
